      "Text": "[llm] system: %buildGoalPrompt%\n        user: %goalForLlm%\n         scheme: {\n            errors?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n            warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n            steps: [{index: int, approved?: bool, rebuildReason?: string, needsDetail?: bool,\n                  errors?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n                  warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n                  actions?: [{module: string, action: string, parameters?: [{name: string, value?: object}], return?: [{name: string}],\n                              errors?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n                              warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}]}]}]\n                }\n        on error HandleBuildGoalFailure\n        write to %stepResults%",
      "Comment": null,
      "ModuleType": "PLang.Modules.LlmModule",
      "Name": "call_llm_with_structured_response_and_error_handling",
      "Description": "Send a request to the language model using the system prompt stored in %buildGoalPrompt% and the user prompt stored in %goalForLlm%. The response is expected to conform to a detailed JSON schema describing errors, warnings, and steps with nested actions. If an error occurs during the call, the flow should handle it using the HandleBuildGoalFailure step. The final structured response is saved into the %stepResults% variable for further processing.",
